snippet.textDisplay: A theory about menstrual phase locking correlates ovulation with the new moon phase. The increased likelihood of successful reproduction could be due to the tendency for early hominid multi-day hunting parties to correspond with the full moon. Thus, males home for the new moon and some consistency in the periodicity of menstruation with the cycle of phases promotes locking via reproductive success. Just a theory, but one that makes sense and  involves selective measures that are scientifically reliable. No way to prove many theories like this.
